{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775877893646,"sessionID":"ses_2856e336ffferdxwAS5avnd5gd","part":{"id":"prt_d7a922e0a001xO4FnBwrwJP77P","messageID":"msg_d7a921b78001aLlwK5n5lbI196","sessionID":"ses_2856e336ffferdxwAS5avnd5gd","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877939136,"sessionID":"ses_2856e336ffferdxwAS5avnd5gd","part":{"id":"prt_d7a92df5e001QE9wE36FaArO68","messageID":"msg_d7a921b78001aLlwK5n5lbI196","sessionID":"ses_2856e336ffferdxwAS5avnd5gd","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3d3b029327d44baab18d055fa277d2f3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service. The client abstracts underlying HTTP communication, offering a simple, type-safe API for managing agent runtime sessions and invoking agent workloads with minimal boilerplate.\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide a Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service with the following goals:\n\n- Simple, intuitive API for invoking agent runtime workloads\n- Automatic session ID bootstrap and management\n- Context manager support for automatic resource cleanup\n- Integrated Data Plane communication via Router\n- Proper error handling and timeout configuration\n- Detailed logging and debugging support\n\n## Module\n\n`sdk-python`\n\n## Language\n\nPython 3.10+\n\n## Size\n\nM\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeClient Core Functionality**\n   - Session ID bootstrap from Router\n   - Agent workload invocation\n   - Context manager support (`__enter__` / `__exit__`)\n   - Resource cleanup\n\n2. **Data Plane Integration**\n   - HTTP communication via Router\n   - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n   - Timeout configuration\n   - Connection pooling\n\n3. **Configuration Management**\n   - Environment variable resolution (`ROUTER_URL`)\n   - Configurable timeouts (read, connect)\n   - Session ID reuse support\n\n4. **Error Handling**\n   - Session validation\n   - HTTP error propagation\n   - Clear error messages\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Agent lifecycle management (create, delete, list)\n- Session persistence and recovery\n- Streaming responses\n- Webhook support\n- Metrics and observability\n- Async API (can be added in future AR)\n- Custom retry logic\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Components Impacted\n\n1. **Python SDK Package Structure**\n   - New file: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n   - New file: `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n   - Update `agentcube/__init__.py` exports\n\n2. **Router Service (Data Plane)**\n   - GET `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Bootstrap session ID\n   - POST `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Invoke agent\n\n3. **Developer Experience**\n   - Provide Python SDK documentation\n   - Example code for agent invocation\n   - pip package distribution\n\n4. **Testing and CI/CD**\n   - Unit tests for client classes\n   - Integration tests with Router\n   - E2E testing\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `requests ^2.31.0` - HTTP client\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This is a new SDK feature.\n\n### Security Considerations\n\n1. **Authentication**\n   - Router handles JWT validation\n   - Session ID transmitted via headers\n   - No auth token directly set by SDK\n\n2. **Data Transmission**\n   - HTTPS recommended (production)\n   - Session ID via `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n   - Payloads as JSON\n\n3. **Input Validation**\n   - Session ID validation before invoke\n   - Type checking via Python type hints\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### HTTP Client Selection\n\n**Choice**: `requests.Session`\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Mature and widely-used HTTP client\n- Built-in connection pooling\n- Simple, intuitive API\n- Good documentation and community support\n\n### Session Management Strategy\n\n**Choice**: Bootstrap session ID via GET request\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Router manages session lifecycle\n- No Control Plane involvement needed\n- Simple and stateless\n- Supports session reuse\n\n**Implementation**:\n1. `AgentRuntimeClient` initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n2. If `session_id` not provided, call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n3. GET on invocation URL returns `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n4. POST requests use the session ID header\n\n### Timeout Configuration Strategy\n\n**Choice**: Configurable defaults with per-call override\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Different workloads have different timeout needs\n- Support global defaults\n- Allow per-invocation override\n\n**Configuration**:\n1. Default connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n2. Default read timeout: 120 seconds\n3. Invoke method accepts optional `timeout` parameter\n4. Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n**Choice**: Standard exceptions with clear messages\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Python's exception hierarchy is sufficient\n- `requests` provides detailed HTTP errors\n- Custom `ValueError` for missing session ID\n- Simpler than custom exception hierarchy\n\n### Configuration Resolution Strategy\n\n**Choice**: Parameter priority over environment variables\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Provide flexibility\n- Support different deployment scenarios\n- Ease of testing\n\n**Priority**:\n1. Constructor parameters\n2. Environment variable (`ROUTER_URL`)\n3. Default values\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Async HTTP Client\n\n**Description**: Use `httpx` or `aiohttp` for async API\n\n**Pros**:\n- Supports async operations\n- Better concurrency for I/O-bound tasks\n\n**Cons**:\n- Steeper learning curve\n- More complex integration\n- Not needed for initial use cases\n\n**Decision**: Rejected - Sync API sufficient for v1, can extend later\n\n### Alternative 2: gRPC Protocol\n\n**Description**: Use gRPC instead of HTTP REST\n\n**Pros**:\n- Efficient binary protocol\n- Strong typing\n- Built-in streaming support\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires server-side gRPC support\n- More complex deployment\n- Harder to debug\n\n**Decision**: Rejected - HTTP REST is more universal and easier to integrate\n\n### Alternative 3: Single Client Class\n\n**Description**: Merge Data Plane into main client\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler API\n- Fewer files\n\n**Cons**:\n- Violates single responsibility principle\n- Harder to test\n- Less flexible\n\n**Decision**: Rejected - Separate Data Plane client is cleaner\n\n### Alternative 4: Control Plane Session Management\n\n**Description**: Use Control Plane for session creation\n\n**Pros**:\n- Consistent with CodeInterpreterClient\n\n**Cons**:\n- Unnecessary complexity\n- Router already handles sessions\n- Extra dependencies\n\n**Decision**: Rejected - Router-only approach is simpler\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Data Plane Client (Day 1)\n\n1. Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n2. Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method\n3. Implement `invoke()` method\n4. Implement `close()` method\n5. Add unit tests\n\n### Phase 2: Agent Runtime Client (Day 1-2)\n\n1. Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n2. Implement constructor and configuration resolution\n3. Implement context manager (`__enter__` / `__exit__`)\n4. Implement `invoke()` method\n5. Implement `close()` method\n6. Add unit tests\n\n### Phase 3: Integration and Testing (Day 2)\n\n1. Update `agentcube/__init__.py` exports\n2. Integration tests with Router\n3. E2E testing\n4. Error scenario testing\n\n### Phase 4: Documentation (Day 2-3)\n\n1. Write API documentation\n2. Create usage examples\n3. Update README\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Tests**\n   - Session ID bootstrap\n   - Invoke request construction\n   - Session header management\n   - Timeout handling\n   - Error propagation\n\n2. **AgentRuntimeClient Tests**\n   - Configuration resolution\n   - Session ID initialization\n   - Context manager behavior\n   - Invoke delegation\n   - Cleanup\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **Router Integration Tests**\n   - Bootstrap session ID from real Router\n   - Invoke with real payload\n   - Session header validation\n   - Timeout scenarios\n\n2. **E2E Tests**\n   - Complete usage flow\n   - Context manager lifecycle\n   - Error recovery\n\n### Mock Tests\n\n1. **HTTP Request Mock**\n   - Use `responses` or similar to mock HTTP\n   - Test various response scenarios\n   - Test error conditions\n\n## API Specification\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: str | None = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: str | None = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ) -> None\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n\n    def invoke(self, payload: dict[str, object], timeout: float | None = None) -> dict[str, object]\n\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str\n\n    def invoke(self, session_id: str, payload: dict[str, Any], timeout: float | None = None) -> requests.Response\n\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n### HTTP Endpoints\n\n- `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Bootstrap session ID\n  - Returns: `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n\n- `POST {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Invoke agent\n  - Headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n  - Body: JSON payload\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Router service URL | Required |\n\n### Constructor Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | str | Required | Agent runtime name |\n| `namespace` | str | \"default\" | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `router_url` | str \\| None | None | Router URL |\n| `verbose` | bool | False | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | str \\| None | None | Existing session ID to reuse |\n| `timeout` | int | 120 | Read timeout in seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | float | 5.0 | Connect timeout in seconds |\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n1. **Connection Pooling**\n   - `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter`\n   - Default pool size: 10\n   - Reduces connection overhead\n\n2. **Timeout Configuration**\n   - Reasonable defaults\n   - Prevents indefinite hangs\n   - Per-call override support\n\n3. **Session Reuse**\n   - Existing `session_id` can be passed\n   - Avoids extra GET request\n   - Multiple invocations share session\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Session Management**\n   - Router handles session validation\n   - Session ID transmitted via headers\n   - No auth token directly managed\n\n2. **Input Validation**\n   - Session ID checked before invoke\n   - Type hints for API contracts\n   - Payloads must be JSON-serializable\n\n3. **Logging Security**\n   - No sensitive data in logs\n   - Session ID may be logged (consider filtering)\n\n## Monitoring and Metrics\n\n### Key Metrics\n\n1. **Client Metrics**\n   - Request count\n   - Request latency\n   - Error rate\n\n2. **Session Metrics**\n   - Session bootstrap count\n   - Session reuse count\n\n3. **Invocation Metrics**\n   - Invocation count\n   - Success rate\n   - Invocation latency\n\n### Logging\n\n1. **Request Logs**\n   - HTTP requests/responses\n   - Session IDs\n   - Timestamps\n\n2. **Error Logs**\n   - Error types\n   - Error messages\n   - Stack traces\n\n3. **Debug Logs**\n   - Configuration details\n   - Session bootstrap\n   - Request details\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Q1**: Should we implement retry logic for transient failures?\n   - **Current**: No retry logic\n   - **Discussion**: Could improve reliability\n   - **Decision**: Not in v1, can be added later\n\n2. **Q2**: Should we support async API?\n   - **Current**: Sync-only\n   - **Discussion**: Async may improve performance for concurrent invocations\n   - **Decision**: Not in v1, can be added later\n\n3. **Q3**: Should we expose metrics?\n   - **Current**: No metrics collection\n   - **Discussion**: Would help with observability\n   - **Decision**: Not in v1, can be added later\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n- Integration tests pass with real Router\n- API documentation complete and accurate\n- Example code works end-to-end\n- Performance meets requirements (P99 latency < 200ms)\n- Zero security vulnerabilities\n- Package publishes successfully to PyPI\n\n## References\n\n- [Python SDK Design](../../python-sdk/design.md)\n- [Python SDK Spec](../../python-sdk/spec.md)\n- [Requests Documentation](https://requests.readthedocs.io/)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [16:25] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\nERROR [18:25] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\nERROR [78:65] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py\">\nERROR [82:24] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\n</diagnostics>","